<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-07-30T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-07-30T16:00:00-05:00" n="636" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d636">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">821.6363 Barco/122: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Piles</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-07-30T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">July 30,
                                        1928—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 8:55
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>62. Department’s 40, July 27, 6 p.m. Delivered note to Minister of
                            Foreign Affairs today. He expressed approval of its contents. Impossible
                            to see President today but hope to have interview tomorrow.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Piles</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>